        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Job 11</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" />
                        <l n="1" xml:id="Job-011-001"><seg type="commented" corresp="#Job--seg001"
                                 /><supplied reason="lost">Da qaruv berdi Cofar ol Naʿamati da
                                ajtty.</supplied><anchor type="commented" xml:id="Job--seg001"
                                 /><ref n="1" target="#Job-011-fn1" type="noteAnchor" /></l>
                        <l n="2" xml:id="Job-011-002">Köp sözlergemo qaruv berilmesti da jemese köp
                            sözler jesisi rast čyɣarmo.</l>
                        <l n="3" xml:id="Job-011-003">Aldavlaryn elni tyjyltadylar da elik etsen da
                            joḥtu imendirivčü.</l>
                        <l n="4" xml:id="Job-011-004">Da ajtasen Tenrige aruvdu aqylym da paq edim
                            ʿenajatlarynda.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="32v" />
                        <milestone unit="line" />
                        <l n="5" xml:id="Job-011-005">Da kertiden kim bersejedi ki Tenri sözlegej
                                <seg type="commented" corresp="#Job--seg002" />da klegej<anchor
                                type="commented" xml:id="Job--seg002" /><ref n="2"
                                target="#Job-011-fn2" type="noteAnchor" /> da ki ačqaj bujruqlaryn
                            birgene.</l>
                        <l n="6" xml:id="Job-011-006">Da anlatqajedi sana jasyrynlyqlaryn usnun ki
                            eki anča qatlanɣajedi ol abrajlyq da bilgin ki unutturɣajedi <seg
                                type="commented" corresp="#Job--seg003" /><foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או תאמ׳ </foreign>
                            eksitkejedi<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Job--seg003" /><ref n="3"
                                target="#Job-011-fn3" type="noteAnchor" /> sana Tenri jazyɣyndan
                                <seg type="commented" corresp="#Job--seg004" /><foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או תאמ׳ </foreign>
                            borčlu etkejedi<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Job--seg004" /><ref
                                n="4" target="#Job-011-fn4" type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <l n="7" xml:id="Job-011-007">Tergevinmo Tenrinin jetersen jemese
                            tügelliginede dejin küčlü Tenrinin jetersen.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="33r" />
                        <milestone unit="line" />
                        <l n="8" xml:id="Job-011-008">Bijiklik<addSpan spanTo="#Job-011-add001"
                                 />l<anchor xml:id="Job-011-add001" type="addSpan" />erine köklernin
                            ne qylarsen törenrekni<ref n="5" target="#Job-011-fn5" type="noteAnchor"
                             /> gerden ne bilisen.</l>
                        <l n="9" xml:id="Job-011-009">Uzunraqty jerden ölčevi anyn da könligi<ref
                                n="6" target="#Job-011-fn6" type="noteAnchor" /> tengizden.</l>
                        <l n="10" xml:id="Job-011-010">Eger kesse da beklejdi da yštyrsa da kim
                            qajta alyr any.</l>
                        <l n="11" xml:id="Job-011-011">Ki ol biledi išlerin jalɣan elnin da baqsa
                            avančy kiši üstüne da esin qojmajdy jollaryna.</l>
                        <l n="12" xml:id="Job-011-012">Da eksik aqylly kiši aqyllanady da
                            <milestone unit="page" n="33v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" />
                            kijik at kibik adam tuvdurulady.</l>
                        <l n="13" xml:id="Job-011-013">Eger sen tüzüsejedin jüreginni da jajsajedin
                            anar uvučlarynny.</l>
                        <l n="14" xml:id="Job-011-014">Eger avanlyqny ki bardy qolunda jyraq
                            ketersejedin any da toḥtatmasajedin üvünde avanlyqny.</l>
                        <l n="15" xml:id="Job-011-015">Ki ol vaḥtyna balqytqajedin jüzlerinni
                            ajyptan da bolɣajedin kip da qorqmaɣajedin.</l>
                        <l n="16" xml:id="Job-011-016">Ki sen bu ömgeklikni unutqajedin
                            <milestone unit="page" n="34r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" />
                            suvlar kibik ki astylar saɣynɣajedin.</l>
                        <l n="17" xml:id="Job-011-017">Da edirek tüš vaḥtlardan janɣyrɣajedi zamanyn
                            da balquvu kibik tannyn bolɣajedin.</l>
                        <l n="18" xml:id="Job-011-018">Da išanɣajedin ki bardy umsunč da qyjasa
                            qazylyp jerge eminlikbyla tynč jatqajedin.</l>
                        <l n="19" xml:id="Job-011-019">Da qajtqajedin da bolmaɣajedi qaltratuvču da
                            qolɣajediler jüzleri<addSpan spanTo="#Job-011-add002" />nni<anchor
                                xml:id="Job-011-add002" type="addSpan" /> köpler.</l>
                        <l n="20" xml:id="Job-011-020">Kertiden közleri rašaʿlarnyn ham ki
                            <milestone unit="page" n="34v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" />
                            tölmerselerde<ref n="7" target="#Job-011-fn7" type="noteAnchor" />
                            umsunč taspolady alardan ysančlary alarnyn sismegi <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Job--seg005" /><foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            syzlavu<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Job--seg005" /><ref n="8"
                                target="#Job-011-fn8" type="noteAnchor" /> ǯannyn.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="Job-011-fn1" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: The Karaim equivalent
                            of the standard Hebrew Job 11:1 is not included in the text, probably
                            intentionally, see Job 3:1, 4:1, etc. for similar cases. The text is
                            reconstructed here on the basis of Job 2:11 and ms. ADub.III.84. The
                            Hebrew text is not omitted, see BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וַיַּעַן צֹפַר הַנַּעֲמָתִי וַיֹּאמַר </foreign>
                            ‘Then Zophar the Naamathite answered and said’ (Job 11:1). | C: <emph>Da
                                ǯoɣap berdi Čofar ol Naʿamatly da ajtty</emph>. | QB: <emph>Da ǯoɣap
                                berdi Čofar ol Naʿamatly da ajtty</emph>. | ADub.III.84: <emph>Da
                                qaruv berdi Cofar ol Naʿamaly da ajtty</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                                <emph>Da qaruv berdi Cofar ol Naʿamatly da ajtty</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-011-fn2" type="footnote">Initially: <emph>klegej
                            da</emph>; the order of these two words was corrected by the copyist by
                            numbering them with <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;"
                                >א </foreign>
                            and ב, respectively.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-011-fn3" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>unutturɣajedi</emph>, the equivalent of BHeb. <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">יַשֶּׁה </foreign>
                            ‘exacts’. It is introduced with the Hebrew phrase <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או תאמ׳ </foreign>
                            ‘or you will say’; <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;"
                                >תאמ׳ </foreign>
                            is an abbreviation for <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">תאמר</foreign>
                            . | C: <emph>unutturdy bolɣaj</emph>. | QB: <emph>unutturdy
                                bolɣaj</emph>. | ADub.III.84: <emph>unutturɣajedi</emph> or
                                <emph>eksitkejedi</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                                <emph>unutturadyr</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-011-fn4" type="footnote">It is not entirely clear the
                            alternative translation of which passage is this portion of text. It is
                            introduced with the Hebrew phrase <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או תאמ׳ </foreign>
                            ‘or you will say’; <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;"
                                >תאמ׳ </foreign>
                            is an abbreviation for <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">תאמר</foreign>
                            .</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-011-fn5" type="footnote">Hypercorrect form of
                                <emph>terenrekni</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-011-fn6" type="footnote">Hypercorrect form of
                                <emph>kenligi</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-011-fn7" type="footnote">Hypercorrect form of
                                <emph>telmerselerde</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-011-fn8" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>sismegi</emph>, written after Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            ‘or’; it has no exact equivalent in the standard Hebrew text. | C:
                                <emph>syzlovy</emph>. | QB: <emph>syzlovy</emph>. | ADub.III.84:
                                <emph>syzlavyna</emph>; different wording. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                                <emph>tuzahy</emph>.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
